Religious leaders have arrived in Nkandla to pray for the former president. Siphamandla Goge has more. #DStv403 NKANDLA - Former President Jacob Zuma is reportedly in Durban consulting with his lawyers on the Constitutional Court judgment. Zuma has three days left to hand himself over to authorities. WATCH: Zuma could be granted reprieve He was found to be in contempt of court for his consistent refusal to appear before the State Capture Inquiry. The Jacob Zuma Foundation is denouncing the judgment calling it emotional and angry. Religious leaders have arrived in Nkandla to pray for former President Jacob Zuma.